Looking at the code, I can see the issue clearly in `format-workspace.tsx` at lines 268-278:

```typescript
const doCopy = async (content: string, isHtml: boolean) => {
  try {
    if (isHtml) {
      const blob = new Blob([content], { type: "text/html" });
      const plainBlob = new Blob([content], { type: "text/plain" });  // <-- PROBLEM
      await navigator.clipboard.write([
        new ClipboardItem({
          "text/html": blob,
          "text/plain": plainBlob,
        }),
      ]);
```

The `plainBlob` is created from the raw HTML `content` instead of extracting plain text. When pasting into a plain-text context (like a text editor), users see raw HTML tags instead of readable text.

This is confirmed in the PR diff—the file was modified but this exact issue persists.

