Fix a security vulnerability in `/Users/philippbriese/Documents/dev/chat exporter/apps/server/src/lib/clipboard-import.ts`.

**Problem:** Line 70 uses `new JSDOM(html, { runScripts: "dangerously" })` on untrusted user-submitted clipboard HTML. This executes any `<script>` tags in the pasted HTML in the Node.js process — a server-side RCE vulnerability.

**Fix:** Change to `runScripts: "outside-only"` and inject the DOM_KIT_SCRIPT via `window.eval()` instead of creating a `<script>` element. With `"outside-only"`, scripts in the parsed HTML won't execute, but programmatic `window.eval()` calls will work.

Replace:
```ts
const dom = new JSDOM(html, { runScripts: "dangerously" });
const { window } = dom;

// Inject DOM kit script into JSDOM
const scriptEl = window.document.createElement("script");
scriptEl.textContent = DOM_KIT_SCRIPT;
window.document.head.appendChild(scriptEl);
```

With:
```ts
const dom = new JSDOM(html, { runScripts: "outside-only" });
const { window } = dom;

// Inject DOM kit helpers via eval — "outside-only" prevents user-supplied
// scripts from executing while allowing programmatic injection.
window.eval(DOM_KIT_SCRIPT);
```

After fixing, stage ONLY the changed file and commit:
```
fix(server): prevent RCE via JSDOM runScripts on clipboard HTML

JSDOM was initialized with runScripts: "dangerously" which executes
any <script> tags in user-submitted clipboard HTML in the Node.js
process. Switch to "outside-only" and inject the DOM kit via
window.eval() so only our helper script runs, not attacker-supplied
code.
```

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>

