Fix an inconsistency in `/Users/philippbriese/Documents/dev/chat exporter/apps/server/src/lib/artifact-generators.ts`.

**Problem:** `ArtifactGeneratorRegistry.register()` (line 30-32) silently overwrites on duplicate registration via `Map.set()`, while the sibling `FormatRegistry` in `packages/shared/src/output-formats.ts` throws on duplicate. These are companion registries in the same pluggable-format feature with opposite contracts.

**Fix:** Add a duplicate guard to `ArtifactGeneratorRegistry.register()`:
```ts
register(generator: ArtifactGenerator): void {
  if (this.generators.has(generator.formatId)) {
    throw new Error(
      `Artifact generator for format "${generator.formatId}" is already registered.`,
    );
  }
  this.generators.set(generator.formatId, generator);
}
```

Also update the test file `apps/server/src/lib/artifact-generators.test.ts` — find the test that says "registering a generator with duplicate formatId overwrites the previous one" and change it to verify that duplicate registration throws instead:
```ts
test("registering a generator with duplicate formatId throws", () => {
  const registry = new ArtifactGeneratorRegistry();
  registry.register(markdownGenerator);
  expect(() => registry.register(markdownGenerator)).toThrow(
    'Artifact generator for format "markdown" is already registered.',
  );
});
```

After fixing, stage ONLY the two changed files and commit:
```
fix(server): add duplicate guard to ArtifactGeneratorRegistry

ArtifactGeneratorRegistry silently overwrote on duplicate registration
while the sibling FormatRegistry throws. Align the contract so both
registries reject accidental double-registration consistently.
```

